acknowledgements.message: A current Virtual Connect Manager configuration backup must be created. Virtual Connect Manager will not be available after the migration.
Any OneView resources created by or used during this migration must not be modified until the migration has completed.

issues.description: The SNMP configuration has Virtual Connect Manager trap categories selected that are not supported by OneView.
issues.recommendation: Virtual Connect Manager trap categories contains Domain Status, FC Status, Server Status, Network Status, Profile Status, Fabric Status, and Enet Status which are not supported by OneView. These categories will be removed.

issues.description: SMI-S is disabled.
issues.recommendation: SMI-S will be enabled automatically.

items.description: Logical interconnect group for bays 1,2,3,4,5 and 6.

issues.description: The shared uplink set "UplinkSet1longlong02longlong03longlong04longlong05longlong06long" has no uplinks and a connection mode of failover; this configuration is not supported by OneView.
issues.recommendation: The connection mode will automatically be changed to automatic.

issues.description: The shared uplink set "UplinkSetNative" has no uplinks and a connection mode of failover; this configuration is not supported by OneView.
issues.recommendation: The connection mode will automatically be changed to automatic.

issues.recommendation: If it is acceptable for this connection to not be migrated to the OneView server profile, proceed with the migration. {"name":"Learn more","uri":"/doc#/cic/enclosure/migrate/unassigned/connect/learn"}

issues.description: One or more connections for profile "Profile1" are configured with Use-BIOS boot settings. OneView does not support profile connections configured with a mixture of Use-BIOS and other boot settings.
issues.recommendation: The Virtual Connect Use-BIOS boot setting will be automatically changed to "not bootable" when the profile is migrated to OneView. If this change is acceptable, proceed with the migration.
